{"type":"message","id":"6af02a38","parentId":"45c4bc18","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:57:43.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the experiment file that was actually created and the most recent pulse log.","thinkingSignature":"84d442f97cdb9f92816c00219759c5113d5c192116a44892395d047eb9064b87"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oy5viq5wby2t_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oy5viq5wby2t_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 155617.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2193,"output":113,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14551,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774382260380}}
{"type":"message","id":"ddc860b1","parentId":"6af02a38","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:57:43.519Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oy5viq5wby2t_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Hybrid CFIÃ—Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\n**Status:** RUNNING\n\n## Experiment Design\n\n### Hypothesis\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freqâ‰ˆ160, CFI=1) â†’ score â‰ˆ 1.0 Ã— 1.0 = 1.0 BUT capped at freq/120 = 160/120 = 1.33 â†’ min(1, 1.33) = 1.0 â†’ score = 1.0\n- Favor research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) â†’ moderate score based on both dimensions\n- Distinguish \"for next instantiation\" from \"Phase 1\" based on frequency normalization\n\n### Formula Implementation\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * freq_normalized\n```\n\n### Token Scoring Examples\n| Token | CFI | Freq | freq/120 | Hybrid Score | Classification |\n|-------|-----|------|----------|--------------|----------------|\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.33â†’1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"pulse\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"completed at:\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"Phase 1\" | 0.96 | 136 | 1.13â†’1.0 | 0.96 | Trajectory (allow) |\n| \"research\" | 0.75 | 80 | 0.67 | 0.50 | Trajectory (allow) |\n| \"architecture\" | 0.60 | 40 | 0.33 | 0.20 | Trajectory (allow) |\n\n### Key Insight\nThe min(1, freq/120) caps the frequency contribution, so even freq=160 tokens score at most 1.0 on the frequency axis, but they still get the CFI bonus. Waitâ€”that's not right for penalizing constants.\n\n### Revised Formula Logic\nActually, we want HIGH scores for research trajectory tokens and LOW scores for constants. Let's reconsider:\n\nIf freq(T) = 160 (constants):\n- min(1, 160/120) = 1.0\n- CFI(constants) â‰ˆ 1.0\n- score = 1.0 Ã— 1.0 = 1.0 (HIGH)\n\nIf freq(T) = 40 (research tokens):\n- min(1, 40/120) = 0.33\n- CFI(research) â‰ˆ 0.60\n- score = 0.60 Ã— 0.33 = 0.20 (LOW)\n\nThis is BACKWARDS. High scores go to constants.\n\n### Corrected Formula for Penalizing Constants\nWe want constants to score LOW:\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    freq_penalty = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_penalty)  # Low freq â†’ high score, High freq â†’ low score\n```\n\nNow:\n- freq=160: score = 1.0 Ã— (1 - 1.0) = 0.0 (PENALIZED)\n- freq=40: score = 0.6 Ã— (1 - 0.33) = 0.6 Ã— 0.67 = 0.40 (REWARDED)\n\n### Final Formula\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    \"\"\"\n    score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— (1 - min(1, freq(T)/120))\n    \n    High CFI + Low freq = HIGH score (research trajectory)\n    High CFI + High freq = LOW score (constant format)\n    \"\"\"\n    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_normalized)\n```\n\n## Experiment Results (TBD)\nWill run on 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:42:02\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\n# Testing: score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— min(1, freq(T)/120)\n\n## Hypothesis\nThe hybrid formula should:\n- De-weight constant-format tokens (freqâ‰ˆ160, CFI=1.00 â†’ scoreâ‰ˆ1.0 Ã— 1.0 = 1.0, but freq/120=1.33 capped at 1.0)\n- Properly score research trajectory tokens (freq=60, CFI=0.7 â†’ score=0.7 Ã— 0.5 = 0.35)\n- Better distinguish signal from metaprogramming noise\n\n## Method\n- 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split\n- Strategy A: Binary thresholds (CFI â‰¥ 0.5 AND freq âˆˆ [3, 120))\n- Strategy C: Hybrid score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— min(1, freq(T)/120)\n- Metric: Precision, Recall, F1 for identifying \"important\" tokens\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Implement scoring formulas\n- [ ] Run on pulse corpus\n- [ ] Compare precision/recall curves\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C Validation\nGenerated: 2026-03-24\n\n## Objective\nTest hypothesis: `score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— min(1, freq(T)/120)` distinguishes:\n- Constant format (freqâ‰ˆ160, CFIâ‰ˆ1, scoreâ‰ˆ1.0) â†’ metaprogramming artifact\n- Research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5, score>0.4) â†’ true causal content\n\n## Experiment Design\n- Dataset: 200 pulses from corpus\n- Train/Test split: 80/20\n- Metric: Precision and recall for research trajectory identification\n\n## Token Categories (from CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md)\n| Token | Freq | CFI | Score | Classification |\n|-------|------|-----|-------|----------------|\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\n| \"completed at:\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | constant-format (expected to filter) |\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n| \"Phase 0\" | 85 | 0.89 | 0.74 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n| \"CFI\" | 112 | 0.72 | 0.60 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n| \"architecture\" | 45 | 0.68 | 0.23 | research trajectory (KEEP) |\n\n## Scoring Formula\n\n\n## Hypothesis Test\nIf score > 0.4 â†’ classify as research trajectory\nExpected result:\n- Constant format (freq=160, CFI=1): score=1.0 (BUT these should be manually tagged)\n- Research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5): score > 0.4 (KEEP)\n\n## KEY INSIGHT\nThe hybrid scoring does NOT filter constant-format tokens (they score high).\nThese need a SEPARATE filter: freq >= 150 as \"metaprogramming contamination\".\nFinal filter: (score > 0.4) AND (freq < 150)\n\"\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Strategy C: Hybrid CFIÃ—Freq Scoring Experiment\n\n## Hypothesis\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) Ã— min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freqâ‰ˆ160, CFI=1.0): score â‰ˆ 1.0 Ã— 1.0 = 1.0 (BUT capped at 1.0 means we need freqâ‰¥120)\n- Actually: score = 1.0 Ã— min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 Ã— 0.87 = 0.87\n- Reward research trajectory tokens (freq=80, CFI=0.8): score = 0.8 Ã— 0.67 = 0.53\n- Penalize rare tokens (freq=3, CFI=0.6): score = 0.6 Ã— 0.025 = 0.015\n\n## Problem Identified\nThe min(1, freq/120) caps at 1.0 for freqâ‰¥120, meaning constant-format tokens get score â‰ˆ 0.87-1.0.\nThis DOES NOT distinguish them from research tokens (freq=136, CFI=0.96) â†’ score = 0.96.\n\n## Revised Formula\n\n\nThis adds a hard cutoff at freq=150 to exclude constant-format tokens entirely.\n\n## Experiment Protocol\n1. Extract CFI and frequency for all tokens from pulse corpus\n2. Compute three scoring methods:\n   - A: CFI â‰¥ 0.5 (baseline)\n   - B: CFI â‰¥ 0.5 AND 3 â‰¤ freq < 120 (three-dimensional filter)\n   - C: score = CFI Ã— min(1, freq/120) AND freq < 150 (hybrid)\n3. Evaluate on 200 pulses (160 train / 40 test)\n4. Metrics: precision, recall, F1 against human-identified research tokens\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C\n\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\n**Status:** DESIGNED - Ready to run\n\n## Hypothesis\nHybrid score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) will:\n- De-weight constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.00 → score≈1.0 but normalized)\n- Preserve research tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5 → score scales with CFI)\n- NOT need binary thresholds\n\n## Test Design\n1. **Dataset:** Same 200 pulses, 80/20 split\n2. **Comparison:** Hybrid scores vs binary thresholds (CFI≥0.5, freq∈[3,120))\n3. **Validation:** Manual inspection of top-scored tokens\n\n## Expected Outcome\n| Token Type | Freq | CFI | Binary Pass | Hybrid Score |\n|------------|------|-----|-------------|--------------|\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | ✗ (freq≥120) | 1.00 |\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | ✗ (freq≥120) | 0.80 |\n| \"architecture\" | 45 | 0.72 | ✓ | 0.27 |\n| \"compression\" | 23 | 0.65 | ✓ | 0.12 |\n\n## Key Metric\nDoes hybrid scoring push research tokens (freq 30-120) above constant-format noise floor?\n\n**Run command:**\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\n**Type:** Strategy C - Hybrid Scoring\n**Goal:** Test if score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) distinguishes constant-format from research trajectory\n\n## Experiment Design\n\n### Hypothesis\nThe hybrid formula will:\n1. **Dampen constant-format tokens**: score(\"for next instantiation\") = 1.0 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 (still high!)\n2. **Preserve research tokens**: score(\"Phase 1\") = 0.96 × min(1, 136/120) = 0.96 (unchanged)\n3. **Reward mid-frequency causal tokens**: score(\"temporal attention\") = 0.7 × min(1, 40/120) = 0.7 × 0.33 = 0.23\n\n**Problem detected:** The formula still doesn't penalize freq=160 tokens enough!\n\n### Revised Formula\nTo truly separate constant-format from research:\n\n\n### Test Plan\n1. Extract all tokens from 200 pulses\n2. Compute: CFI(T), freq(T), hybrid_score(T)\n3. Compare token distributions across three categories:\n   - **Constant-format** (expected: freq>140, CFI>0.95)\n   - **Research trajectory** (expected: 3≤freq≤120, CFI>0.5)\n   - **Noise** (expected: freq<3 OR freq>140 AND CFI<0.5)\n4. Evaluate precision/recall vs ground truth from Strategy A/B\n\n## Results (In Progress)\n*To be filled after running on pulse corpus*\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382263518}}
{"type":"message","id":"99c0ac7b","parentId":"ddc860b1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:57:43.522Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oy5viq5wby2t_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 155617\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful action for this pulse.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent synthesis:\r\n\r\n1. **CFI Compression Experiment is COMPLETE** - we have the analysis showing CFI×Freq hybrid is the right approach\r\n2. **Next immediate step**: Run the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n   - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n   - Test against binary thresholds\r\n   - 200 pulses, 80/20 split\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that the \"Constant Format Problem\" tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts that need to be filtered. The hybrid formula should distinguish these from true research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action is to **implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment**. This directly follows from the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md findings.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Create a pulse analysis script that implements the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Run it on the 200 pulses\r\n3. Compare results against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nOr, I could update the research document to specify the exact experimental design for the next phase, making the pending task concrete.\r\n\r\nGiven that I'm a stateless agent and need to make progress, let me create a concrete experiment spec that can be executed.\r\n\r\nActually, the most efficient single action would be to:\r\n1. Create an experiment runner script that implements the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring\r\n2. This script will process the pulses and generate comparison data\r\n\r\nLet me create `research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1` that implements Strategy C vs the binary threshold strategies.\r\n\r\nWait, I should check what scripts exist. Looking at the context:\r\n- `pulse.ps1` - the main pulse script\r\n- We have `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` with the analysis\r\n\r\nThe most direct action: implement the hybrid scoring experiment to test whether score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) actually distinguishes constant-format from research-trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll craft a PowerShell script to validate the hybrid scoring approach, focusing on extracting precise token characteristics across the pulse dataset.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified the \"Constant Format Problem\" - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.0 are metaprogramming artifacts, not true causal patterns. The next concrete step is to implement and test Strategy C: the hybrid scoring formula.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1` - a script that implements the hybrid scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` and runs a comparison against binary thresholds on the existing 200-pulse dataset. This directly tests whether the hybrid approach distinguishes constant-format from research-trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```powershell\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment - Strategy C vs Binary Thresholds\r\n# Based on: CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md findings\r\n# Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Hypothesis: Hybrid scoring distinguishes constant-format (freq~160, CFI~1) from research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\r\n$pulseDir = \"state/pulses\"\r\n$outputFile = \"research/cfi_hybrid_results.md\"\r\n\r\n# Ensure output directory exists\r\n$pulses = Get-ChildItem $pulseDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name | Select-Object -First 200\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment\"\r\nWrite-Host \"================================\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Testing: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Dataset: $($pulses.Count) pulses\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Aggregate token statistics across all pulses\r\n$tokenStats = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pulse.FullName -Raw\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($token in $tokens) {\r\n        if (-not $tokenStats.ContainsKey($token)) {\r\n            $tokenStats[$token] = @{\r\n                Count = 0\r\n                Occurrences = @()\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        $tokenStats[$token].Count++\r\n        $tokenStats[$token].Occurrences += $pulse.Name\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI and frequency for each token\r\n$analysisResults = @()\r\n$totalTokens = $tokenStats.Values | Measure-Object -Property Count -Sum | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Sum\r\n\r\nforeach ($entry in $tokenStats.GetEnumerator()) {\r\n    $token = $entry.Key\r\n    $stats = $entry.Value\r\n    $freq = $stats.Count\r\n    $occurrences = $stats.Occurrences\r\n    \r\n    # CFI: tokens that appear in EXACTLY the same pulse set\r\n    # Approximation: count how many other tokens share identical occurrence patterns\r\n    $patternKey = ($occurrences | Sort-Object) -join \",\"\r\n    $matchingPatterns = $tokenStats.Values | Where-Object { \r\n        ($_.Occurrences | Sort-Object) -join \",\" -eq $patternKey \r\n    } | Measure-Object\r\n    \r\n    $cfi = [math]::Round($matchingPatterns.Count / $tokenStats.Count, 4)\r\n    \r\n    # Hybrid score: CFI × normalized frequency\r\n    $normalizedFreq = [math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\r\n    $hybridScore = [math]::Round($cfi * $normalizedFreq, 4)\r\n    \r\n    $analysisResults += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Token = $\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:56:40\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382263520}}
