{"type":"message","id":"3480b2bd","parentId":"09bf3ccc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:57:46.203Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_a1bgue98pu2b_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 155714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. The key pending task is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n3. The formula to test is: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n4. This needs to be tested against binary thresholds on 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n\r\nLooking at the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md, I have data showing:\r\n- Binary CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 gives +32.9% precision but loses 92.9% recall\r\n- The constant format problem: tokens like \"for next instantiation\" have freq=160, CFI=1.00 but are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n\r\nThe next action should be to implement and run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me write a script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Computes the hybrid score: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n3. Tests it against binary thresholds on 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n4. Compares precision/recall against the previous binary approach\r\n\r\nThis will test whether the hybrid scoring distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\".\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified that binary thresholds fail due to constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1.0). A hybrid scoring formula was proposed: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120). This needs empirical validation.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nImplement the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment to test whether this formula distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\" better than binary thresholds. Create `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` with the methodology and run analysis on existing pulse data.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment\r\n\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\r\n**Strategy:** Hybrid scoring vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\nBinary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60) fail because:\r\n- **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1.0): \"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\"\r\n  - High CFI × high freq → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (should NOT pass)\r\n- **Research trajectory tokens** (freq≈136, CFI≈0.96): \"Phase 1\"\r\n  - High CFI × high freq → score ≈ 0.96 × 1.0 = 0.96 (should pass)\r\n\r\nBinary threshold logic:\r\n```\r\npass = (CFI >= 0.7) AND (freq < 60)\r\n```\r\n\r\nHybrid scoring formula:\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\npass = score(T) >= threshold\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Key insight:** For constant-format tokens (freq=160), min(1,160/120)=1.0, so score=CFI. For research tokens (freq<120), score is scaled down proportionally.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Data\r\n- 200 pulses from pulse_*.md files\r\n- Split: 160 training / 40 test (80/20)\r\n\r\n### Ground Truth Labels\r\nFrom CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md:\r\n- **Positive:** Research trajectory tokens (Phase 1, architecture, compression, synthesis)\r\n- **Negative:** Metaprogramming artifacts (for next instantiation, pulse, completed at:)\r\n- **Negative:** Common filler (the, and, to, of)\r\n- **Negative:** Low CFI tokens (newly introduced concepts with CFI < 0.3)\r\n\r\n### Methods Compared\r\n\r\n| Method | Formula | Threshold |\r\n|--------|---------|-----------|\r\n| A: Binary CFI | CFI >= 0.7 | 0.7 |\r\n| B: Binary CFI+Freq | (CFI >= 0.7) AND (freq < 60) | - |\r\n| C: Hybrid Score | CFI × min(1, freq/120) | 0.5 |\r\n| D: Hybrid Score | CFI × min(1, freq/120) | 0.4 |\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n- Precision: TP/(TP+FP)\r\n- Recall: TP/(TP+FN)\r\n- F1: 2×P×R/(P+R)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Expected Results\r\n\r\n| Token Type | Freq | CFI | Binary Pass? | Hybrid Score | Hybrid Pass (≥0.5)? |\r\n|------------|------|-----|--------------|--------------|---------------------|\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | NO (freq≥60) | 0.96×1.0=0.96 | YES ✓ |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 89 | 0.85 | YES | 0.85×0.74=0.63 | YES ✓ |\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | NO (freq≥60) | 1.0×1.0=1.0 | YES ✗ (false positive) |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | NO | 1.0×1.0=1.0 | YES ✗ (false positive) |\r\n| \"the\" | 160 | ~0.3 | NO | 0.3×1.0=0.3 | NO ✓ |\r\n\r\n**Problem identified:** Hybrid score alone doesn't solve constant-format problem. Both binary and hybrid treat freq≥120 tokens as high-score\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:57:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382266201}}
